A misty ancient Irish hillside at twilight during the Celtic festival of Samhain, rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures and warm autumn colors. In the foreground, a massive carved turnip lantern glows with ethereal amber light, its flame casting dancing shadows. Behind it, a stone circle stands silhouetted against a sky where the boundary between worlds appears thin—wispy spirits drift upward like autumn leaves caught in wind, their forms translucent and gentle rather than frightening. Scattered around the base of the stones are harvested wheat sheaves, apples, and hazelnuts marking the end of the Celtic year. A family of figures in flowing robes gathers near a bonfire in the middle distance, their silhouettes warm and welcoming. The color palette shifts from deep purples and blues in the sky to rich oranges, golds, and russets in the landscape, capturing that liminal moment between the living world and something ancient and mysterious beyond.
